  "texts": [
    "However, it is important to note that the self-repair capability of current LLMs remains limited and is far less effective than human repair, particularly when dealing with complex project-level errors [142], which suggests significant room for further improvement in this domain.4.1.3 Autonomous Agents and Multi-agent Frameworks.",
    "While Chain-of-Thought and iterative refinement have notably enhanced generation quality, they remain dependent on static context inputs.",
    "To address this limitation, researchers have begun to explore autonomous agent architectures capable of actively acquiring information.",
    "This transition represents a fundamental shift from the \"prompt-response\" paradigm to a \"sense-think-act\" loop.Early explorations achieved preliminary interaction by equipping LLMs with the capability to invoke external tools.",
    "For instance, CoverUp [9] permits the LLM to call a predefined function to actively query the definitions of ambiguous symbols within the current context."
